// src/components/PlayerStatistics.tsx import React from 'react'; import '../../styles/PlayerStatistics.css'; import { BarChart, Bar, LineChart, Line, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, Tooltip, ResponsiveContainer } from 'recharts'; const battingSummary = { matches: 50, runs: 1500, average: 45.2, strikeRate: 90.5, highestScore: 120, }; const bowlingSummary = { matches: 50, wickets: 70, bowlingAverage: 24.3, economyRate: 4.8, bestFigures: '5/30', }; const fieldingSummary = { matches: 50, catches: 25, runOuts: 10, stumpings: 5, }; const performanceData = [ { match: 'Match 1', runs: 30, wickets: 2, catches: 1 }, { match: 'Match 2', runs: 45, wickets: 1, catches: 0 }, { match: 'Match 3', runs: 70, wickets: 3, catches: 2 }, { match: 'Match 4', runs: 20, wickets: 0, catches: 1 }, { match: 'Match 5', runs: 60, wickets: 1, catches: 0 }, ]; const matchResultsData = [ { name: 'Wins', value: 35 }, { name: 'Losses', value: 15 }, ]; const PlayerStatistics: React.FC = () => (

Your Cricket Statistics

{/* Batting Summary */}

Batting Statistics

Matches Played: {battingSummary.matches}

Total Runs: {battingSummary.runs}

Batting Average: {battingSummary.average}

Strike Rate: {battingSummary.strikeRate}

Highest Score: {battingSummary.highestScore}

Performance Graph

{/* Bowling Summary */}

Bowling Statistics

Matches Played: {bowlingSummary.matches}

Wickets Taken: {bowlingSummary.wickets}

Bowling Average: {bowlingSummary.bowlingAverage}

Economy Rate: {bowlingSummary.economyRate}

Best Figures: {bowlingSummary.bestFigures}

Performance Graph

{/* Fielding Summary */}

Fielding Statistics

Matches Played: {fieldingSummary.matches}

Catches Taken: {fieldingSummary.catches}

Run Outs: {fieldingSummary.runOuts}

Stumpings: {fieldingSummary.stumpings}

Performance Graph

{/* Match Results Summary */}

Match Results

Total Wins: {matchResultsData[0].value}

Total Losses: {matchResultsData[1].value}

); export default PlayerStatistics;
